  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2015-09-08T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Student Loan Bankruptcy Parity Act of 2015\n\nThis bill amends the federal bankruptcy code to eliminate the provision that makes certain education debts non-dischargeable in bankruptcy unless repayment imposes an undue hardship.\n\nSpecifically it permits a borrower to discharge in bankruptcy a nonprofit, government, or private student loan, or an obligation to repay an educational benefit, scholarship, or stipend."
